The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 2: The ministry of corporate affairs is looking into the accounts of big corporates with huge turnovers to assess whether these firms are reflecting correctly the losses or gains arising from transactions involving foreign currency in their account books. We are looking into the matter. We will take strict actions if companies are found guilty of misdeed, an official source said.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 2: The founder and chairman of Satyam Computer, B. Ramalinga Raju said he would seriously think about increasing promoters holding or buying back of stock to enhance value for shareholders.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 2: Facing flak for its policies and decisions in the last one year, the communications ministry has decided to broker peace among various warring parties. Communications minister A. Raja is likely to meet all the operators concerned to resolve the disputes.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 2: India has been able to not only retain but also raise its textile exports to the US, notwithstanding the economic slowdown. Exports from China slipped 3.1 per cent, data of the US administration state.                            
	 Paris, Oct. 2: Volkswagen said it would bring its global research and development centre to India, which eventually would produce vehicles for global market. The centre will be set up in Pune, a company official said.                                                                                                                         
